<subSubSection id="02C66578FFF8FFB9FF3D9DD068247F08" pageId="21" pageNumber="35" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFF8FFB9FF3D9DD0686A7C8A" blockId="21.[151,756,404,618]" pageId="21" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFF8FFB9FF3D9DD068057CCD" bold="true" box="[151,264,404,428]" pageId="21" pageNumber="35">Remarks:</emphasis>
The test is strongly convex with rather large area of clear shell material in the umbilical region. The sutures are distinct.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFF8FFB9FF3D9DB768247F08" blockId="21.[151,756,404,618]" pageId="21" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFF8FFB9FF3D9DB768CA7F6A" bold="true" box="[151,455,499,523]" pageId="21" pageNumber="35">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
It is recorded in the Eocene beds and the Esna Shale (LE ROY, 1953). It is recorded in the Maastrichtian and Paleocene zones of the Esh El Mallaha area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
